comments.body:
Thank you [~accountid:62780ad493111000689ece08] ! Just curious--do you know why we are still getting these cases pop up where cardholders who have had their cards for several weeks don’t have access to remittances? In this case, the card was activated May 4. Perhaps a question for [~accountid:5e78fdd1dde7030c4f0d3ddd] ?

Also, perhaps a question for [~accountid:5e78fdd1dde7030c4f0d3ddd] , is there any additional screening we should be doing for these cardholders? We are just asking them if they have the H2A visa, and if they say yes, we are creating support request tickets, but many of these are coming from Lewis, which doesn’t have Hiring (so no I9 on file). Is it safe to assume we can continue with this process of taking the cardholder’s word?

[~accountid:619f24d9ef18ca00712cc620]  I will bring that up in engineering, my understanding is that it should happen during hiring so I’m assuming the hiring process at these farms are not working as it should 

Going further, we need a process for this and we should hold on enabling any more remittances until this process for H2A validation is in place.

!Screenshot 2023-05-26 at 8.41.13.png|width=591,height=73!

Hi [~accountid:613e6eaa1238e8007108f513] Roberto provided an updated list of H2As from this farm, and this cardholder was indeed included. Can you please ensure he still has access? [https://ganazhq.slack.com/archives/C02203LAVM5/p1685044966709369?thread_ts=1685039460.198959&cid=C02203LAVM5|https://ganazhq.slack.com/archives/C02203LAVM5/p1685044966709369?thread_ts=1685039460.198959&cid=C02203LAVM5|smart-link]

[~accountid:619f24d9ef18ca00712cc620]  this CH and all the other ones listed in [https://ganaz.atlassian.net/browse/GAN-5789|https://ganaz.atlassian.net/browse/GAN-5789|smart-link] are now taken care of.
